data.title: Roberts Wesleyan University Athletics
data.meta_description: Brynn King won the NCAA Division II national championship in women's pole vault on May 23.
data.text:
Women's Track & Field 5/30/2024 5:11:00 PM Steve Bradley, Athletic Communications Consultant

Brynn King Named First-Team All-America

ROCHESTER, N.Y. – Brynn King of Roberts Wesleyan University has been named First-Team All-America in NCAA Division II Outdoor Track and Field by the U.S. Track & Field and Cross Country Coaches Association (USTFCCCA).

King set meet and facility records while winning the women's pole vault at the NCAA Division II Outdoor Track and Field Championships on May 23 in Emporia, Kans. King, a junior from The Woodlands, Texas, cleared 4.60 meters (15-feet, 1-inch) to win the event by 7¾ inches.

King, the NCAA Division II Indoor Track and Field champion, set the NCAA Division II outdoor record of 4.68 meters (15-4¼) while winning the Texas Relays on March 30.

King is the first student-athlete from the East Coast Conference to win multiple individual titles and is the first from Roberts to win an NCAA championship. She holds both the NCAA Division II indoor and outdoor records for women's pole vault and was named ECC Female Athlete of the Year in both the indoor and outdoor seasons.

King has qualified for the U.S. Olympic Trials in Eugene, Ore., on June 28 and will receive the Jerry Flynn Award as the Rochester Press-Radio Club's College Athlete of the Year on June 11.
